HELP
.Help

Welcome to the CGIS Executive!

The CGIS Executive provides our Guest Investigators with important
information about the Cosmology Data Analysis Center (CDAC) and also
provides convenient links to the available analytical tools.

But before going any further, one should know how to move around in
text or help screens such as this one.  {BT}Typing an "h" on any{N}
{BT}text/help screen displays a help screen, which explains how to move{N}
{BT}around any text screen in the Executive.{N} Other important items, such
as refreshing or copying the screen, are also discussed.

The Executive includes:

        *  Links to software packages such as UIMAGE, UIDL, IRAF,
           SAOimage, and AIPS

        *  On-line help for all parts of the Executive

        *  On-line documentation, including the CDAC Orientation Handbook,
           the CGIS User's Guide, the Guest Investigator Handbook, and
           instrument specific tutorials

        *  System news


{BT}{U}The Branches of the CGIS Executive Main Menu{N}{N}

{BT}COBE Data and Analysis Menus (UIMAGE)...{N}  Choosing this option
        begins a UIMAGE session.

{BT}Go to Command Line (UIDL){N}  This option begins a session in UIDL.

{BT}Other Analysis Tools...{N}   From this menu, you can access IRAF,
        SAOimage, or AIPS.

{BT}Documentation...{N}   This option contains the on-line versions of the
        CDAC Orientation Handbook and the CGIS User's Guide.  Also,
        information about the hardware at the CDAC, information about
        remote access, and information about how to get a hardcopy of a 
        CDAC document such as the CDAC Handbook, the CGIS User's Guide, 
        the GI Handbook, or any of the instrument specific tutorials.

{BT}News{N}   All users should check this option occasionally to stay
        informed about system or software changes.

{BT}E-Mail{N}   This option puts the user directly into VMS MAIL.

{BT}Shell to Operating System{N}   This option allows the user to 
        return to VMS without disconnecting from the CGIS system.  
        Typing {BT}LOGOUT{N} when finished returns the user to the
        CGIS main menu.

{BT}Gopher{N}   This option connects the user with the GSFC GOPHER 
        facility via Telnet.  Enter {BT}gopher{N} when the {BT}login:{N}
        prompt appears.  Quitting GOPHER returns the user to the CGIS
        main menu.

{BT}Report Problems or Comments{N}   Choosing this invokes the EDT
        editor where you can immediately begin typing in your comment 
        or complaint.  The message will be sent to the appropriate 
        person.

                           {R} End of text. {N}

